article.headline: Lehigh 72, Longwood 57
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- Zahir Carrington and Phil Anderson each had a double-double Sunday, leading Lehigh to a 72-57 victory over Longwood. Carrington finished with a team-high 17 points and a career-best 15 rebounds. Anderson matched his career best with 16 points and added a career-high 12 rebounds for the Mountain Hawks (8-3). Durann Neil hit six 3-pointers and scored 18 points, and Dana Smith added 11 for the Lancers (6-7). Lehigh led 32-19 at halftime. Longwood had 25 fouls, more than double the Mountain Hawks' 11. Lehigh is off to its best start to a season since 1980.
